      "rationale": "Three-level GCI study on systematically refined meshes confirms asymptotic convergence. GCI on NIH < 2.1% on the production mesh (22.1 M cells). Temporal discretization error assessed via halved time-step study; change in cycle-averaged NIH < 0.8%. Both spatial and temporal discretization errors are within accepted bounds for MRL 5 assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted under controlled temperature (37 ± 0.5 °C), hematocrit (35 ± 1%), and inlet flow waveform matching VAD operating envelope. All 5 target operating conditions replicated in experiment. Boundary conditions imposed in CFD are derived directly from experimental measurements with documented uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics (NRMSE, E_rel, Theil U) computed for NIH at all 5 operating points. Monte Carlo 95% prediction intervals enclose all experimental data. Systematic bias < 5% across operating range. Independent statistical review confirmed metric calculations and significance of agreement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which is the direct regulatory metric for hemolysis acceptance. Secondary QoIs (velocity field, wall shear stress) are validated to support mechanistic confidence. Clinical relevance of NIH as a surrogate for chronic hemolysis confirmed by clinical advisory review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the full VAD clinical envelope (3–6 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM). Blood analog fluid properties match clinical hematocrit range. No significant extrapolation beyond validated operating space is required for the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (< 1e-6 for all equations) and cycle-to-cycle variation in NIH (< 0.3% over last 5 cycles). Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic and confirmed negligible relative to discretization error. Solver error budget documented and within MRL 5 tolerance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup independently reproduced by a second analyst from documented simulation plan; results agreed within 1.2% on NIH. Pre-simulation checklist and post-processing scripts version-controlled. User qualification records confirm analyst competency in rotary blood pump CFD. No use errors identified during independent reproduction."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotary blood pump flows. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) evaluated against three alternative formulations; sensitivity of NIH to model form quantified via Sobol indices (total index 0.38). Model form uncertainty included in Monte Carlo UQ ensemble. Selected model form is best-supported by available validation data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (blood viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients, inlet velocity profile, rotational speed) assigned probability distributions based on experimental characterisation or published literature. Monte Carlo sampling (10 000 draws) propagates input uncertainty to NIH. Dominant inputs identified via Sobol analysis. Input distributions peer-reviewed and approved by independent subject matter expert."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments performed with n=5 independent replicates per operating condition using fresh human blood from three donors (hematocrit 33–37%). Inter-replicate and inter-donor variability characterised and incorporated into experimental uncertainty bounds used for output comparison. Sample size justified by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect 10% NIH difference."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
